# goal.md --- Parallel Roadmap to PMP

## Purpose

A structured but flexible roadmap with parallel tracks so progress
continues across multiple areas at once.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CORE PRINCIPLE

You always have: - 1 Primary Phase (main focus) - 2--3 Parallel Tracks
(supporting progress)

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PHASE 1 --- Foundations (Primary)

## Goal

Understand how projects work

### Core Tasks

-   [ ] Learn project vs operations
-   [ ] Learn lifecycle stages
-   [ ] Understand roles

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Parallel Track A --- Practice

-   [ ] Complete 10--20 scenarios
-   [ ] Classify problem types
-   [ ] Explain decisions clearly

## Parallel Track B --- Light Exposure

-   [ ] Watch 2--3 PM overview videos
-   [ ] Read summaries of real projects

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PHASE 2 --- Core Curriculum (Primary)

## Goal

Learn CAPM-aligned knowledge areas

### Core Tasks

-   [ ] Scope
-   [ ] Schedule
-   [ ] Risk
-   [ ] Stakeholders
-   [ ] Agile basics

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Parallel Track A --- Practice

-   [ ] 30--50 scenarios
-   [ ] Identify planning vs execution problems

## Parallel Track B --- Experience Start

-   [ ] Identify small real-world projects
-   [ ] Begin documenting decisions

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PHASE 3 --- Applied Thinking (Primary)

## Goal

Think like a project manager

### Core Tasks

-   [ ] Diagnose before acting
-   [ ] Justify decisions
-   [ ] Handle ambiguity

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Parallel Track A --- Simulation

-   [ ] Build 3--5 full project plans
-   [ ] Run scenario-based simulations

## Parallel Track B --- Experience Growth

-   [ ] Take ownership of tasks/projects
-   [ ] Track outcomes

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PHASE 4 --- Real-World Experience (Primary)

## Goal

Accumulate valid PMP experience

### Core Tasks

-   [ ] Manage small projects
-   [ ] Track scope, schedule, risks
-   [ ] Document decisions

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Parallel Track A --- Resume

-   [ ] Convert work into project language
-   [ ] Add measurable outcomes

## Parallel Track B --- Networking

-   [ ] Connect with PMs
-   [ ] Join communities
-   [ ] Ask questions

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PHASE 5 --- Positioning (Primary)

## Goal

Become hireable as a project professional

### Core Tasks

-   [ ] Build PM-focused resume
-   [ ] Create simple project portfolio

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Parallel Track A --- Applications

-   [ ] Apply to project coordinator roles
-   [ ] Apply to hybrid operations roles

## Parallel Track B --- Continued Learning

-   [ ] Keep scenario practice active
-   [ ] Refine weak areas

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PHASE 6 --- Certification Layer

## CAPM (Optional)

-   [ ] Complete required education hours
-   [ ] Pass CAPM

## PMP (Final Goal)

-   [ ] Accumulate experience
-   [ ] Complete 35 hours training
-   [ ] Apply and pass PMP

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# RULES

1.  Always move forward in primary phase\
2.  Always maintain at least 1 parallel track\
3.  Do not wait for perfection before progressing\
4.  Track real experience as early as possible

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# FINAL OUTCOME

You: - Understand project management deeply - Have real project
experience - Are employable in PM roles - Qualify for PMP certification
